President Obama has signed an Executive Order to create the Task Force on 21st Century Policing, which aims to strengthen community policing and build trust between law enforcement and communities. The Task Force will prepare a report and recommendations to be presented to the President. The President has announced the appointment of several individuals to the Task Force, including Charles H. Ramsey, Commissioner of the Philadelphia Police Department, and Laurie Robinson, Clarence J. Robinson Professor of Criminology, Law and Society at George Mason University. Other appointees include Cedric L. Alexander, Deputy Chief Operating Officer for Public Safety in DeKalb County, Georgia, and Bryan Stevenson, Founder and Executive Director of the Equal Justice Initiative. The Task Force will examine issues such as building public trust and fostering strong relationships between law enforcement and communities, as well as promoting effective crime reduction.